---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout title="The AEGIS Ecosystem" description="A coordinated set of specifications, tools, and documentation — each component with a clear scope and dedicated site.">
  <h1>The AEGIS Ecosystem</h1>

  <section>
    <p>
      AEGIS is a coordinated set of specifications, tools, and documentation.
      Each component has a clear scope and a dedicated site. Together, they form
      a layered architecture that moves from constitutional principles through
      technical governance to runtime enforcement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Three-Layer Architecture</h2>
    <p>
      The AEGIS ecosystem is organized into three reinforcing layers. Each layer
      builds on the one below it, ensuring that governance principles are
      traceable from high-level doctrine all the way to runtime enforcement.
    </p>

    <h3>1. Constitution</h3>
    <p>
      The foundational layer. The <a href="https://aegis-constitution.com">AEGIS Constitution</a>
      defines the immutable principles and articles that all AEGIS-governed AI
      systems must uphold. It is versioned using calendar versioning (CalVer),
      citeable by article and section, and openly licensed. The Constitution is
      the root of authority in the AEGIS ecosystem — every governance decision,
      policy evaluation, and enforcement action traces back to a constitutional
      article.
    </p>

    <h3>2. Governance</h3>
    <p>
      The specification layer. <a href="https://aegis-governance.com">AEGIS Governance</a>
      translates constitutional principles into technical protocols, threat
      taxonomies, and formal specifications. This includes the AGP-1 governance
      protocol, the ATX-1 threat matrix (10 tactics, 29 techniques), and the RFC
      process that governs how the ecosystem evolves. Governance specs are
      published with DOIs for academic citation.
    </p>

    <h3>3. Implementation</h3>
    <p>
      The enforcement layer. The runtime engine (<a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core">aegis-core</a>),
      client SDKs (<a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-sdk">aegis-sdk</a>),
      and operator platform (<a href="https://aegis-platform.net">aegis-platform</a>)
      make governance enforceable in production. Policies defined in the
      governance layer are evaluated deterministically at runtime before any AI
      action is permitted.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Projects &amp; Sites</h2>
    <p>
      Every public-facing component of the AEGIS ecosystem is listed below. Each
      project has its own repository, documentation, and — where applicable — a
      dedicated website.
    </p>

    <div class="eco-grid">
      <a href="https://aegis-constitution.com" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Constitution</h3>
        <p>The canonical governance charter — 11 articles defining the boundaries of AI autonomy. CalVer versioned, citeable, openly licensed.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">aegis-constitution.com</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://aegis-governance.com" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Governance</h3>
        <p>Protocol specifications, threat taxonomy, RFCs, and the ATX-1 threat matrix for agentic AI systems.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">aegis-governance.com</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://aegis-docs.com" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Documentation</h3>
        <p>Developer guides, integration tutorials, and the technical reference for building with AEGIS.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">aegis-docs.com</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://aegis-federation.com" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Federation</h3>
        <p>Cross-domain machine discovery protocol (RFC-0016) for distributed AI governance across organizational boundaries.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">aegis-federation.com</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Core Runtime</h3>
        <p>The Python enforcement engine — a canonical implementation of AGP-1 that evaluates governance policies at runtime.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-sdk" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>SDKs</h3>
        <p>TypeScript and Python client libraries for integrating AEGIS governance into your applications.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-sdk</span>
      </a>

      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-labs" class="eco-card" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <h3>Labs</h3>
        <p>Research sandbox, adversarial testing, and experiments exploring the boundaries of AI governance enforcement.</p>
        <span class="eco-card-domain">github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-labs</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <p>
      For project details, version information, and licensing, see the
      <a href="/ecosystem/projects/">Projects</a> page. For the development
      timeline, see the <a href="/ecosystem/roadmap/">Public Roadmap</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .eco-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .eco-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-text);
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .eco-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .eco-card h3 {
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .eco-card p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .eco-card-domain {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    font-family: "IBM Plex Sans", system-ui, sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1200px) {
    .eco-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .eco-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
